---
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Page title="about -- alexander campos" description="building things to protect how we think.">
  <article>
    <h1>About</h1>

    <p>
      I'm Alex. 26, central Virginia, first-gen Guatemalan American.
    </p>

    <p>
      During the day I work in regulatory operations at Capital One.
      At night I build tools. The impulse is the same in both --
      find where the system breaks and fix it.
    </p>

    <p>
      I broke my spine and femur at 19. Came out of it understanding
      that identity is something you rebuild. That shows up in the work.
    </p>

    <p>
      <a href="/projects/guardian">Guardian</a> started because I
      noticed language models subtly rewriting how I described myself.
      Not overtly -- just enough to shift the framing over time. That
      became a desktop app with a reframe detection engine. Then it
      surfaced a deeper problem, so I started building
      <a href="/projects/forgeframe">ForgeFrame</a> -- middleware
      for keeping your intelligence stack local and yours. The
      <a href="/projects/mcp-memory-server">memory layer</a> is open
      source. The governance layer is not.
    </p>

    <p>
      I'm pursuing a Master of Engineering in Product Innovation.
      I learned Python weeks before I shipped my first working system.
      Started as a bank teller. The work keeps moving.
    </p>

    <p>
      I'm building for a future where the safeguards are as good as the
      tools they're guarding.
    </p>

    <p>
      This site is hand-built. View source if you want to know how.
    </p>

    <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/notaprompt">GitHub</a> -- open source work</li>
      <li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/alexander-d-campos/">LinkedIn</a> -- professional history</li>
      <li><a href="https://substack.com/@alexinthefield">Substack</a> -- writing on identity modeling and system design</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      <a href="mailto:adc.acampos@gmail.com">adc.acampos@gmail.com</a>
    </p>
  </article>

  <script is:inline>
    console.log(
      '%c you are reading about someone building things to protect how we think. ',
      'color: #E8DCC8; font-family: monospace; font-size: 11px;'
    );
  </script>
</Page>

<style>
  .contact-form {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    max-width: 400px;
  }

  .contact-form input,
  .contact-form textarea {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--glow);
    background: var(--depth-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--white-08);
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    outline: none;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .contact-form input::placeholder,
  .contact-form textarea::placeholder {
    color: var(--white-30);
  }

  .contact-form input:focus,
  .contact-form textarea:focus {
    border-color: var(--gold-accent);
  }

  .contact-form textarea {
    resize: vertical;
    min-height: 80px;
  }

  .contact-form button {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--gold-accent);
    background: var(--depth-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--gold-accent);
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    transition: background 0.2s, color 0.2s;
    align-self: flex-start;
  }

  .contact-form button:hover {
    background: var(--gold-accent);
    color: var(--depth-1);
  }
</style>
